<TEXT>
<P>
Regarding David Boatman's complaint about the inane banter between Kelly Lange 
and Fritz Coleman and the others on the 6 p.m. news on KNBC, I have no 
objection to that innocent banter. However, I do object most strenuously to 
having a weatherman who wants to be a comedian and insists on interjecting 
comedy in his weather report. If Coleman wants to be a comedian, he should 
concentrate his efforts on being a comedian. If he wants to be a weather 
reporter, he should concentrate on being a weather reporter. But he should not 
try to be both at the same time. He should not be allowed to force his alleged 
comedic talents on the people who just want to hear the news and weather 
without the comedy. 
</P>
<P>
Howard Longman, Temple City 
</P>
</TEXT>
