<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEIGHBORHOOD NOSHES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
These neighborhood restaurants won't put a dent in your wallet. 
</P>
<P>
Cafe Tartine, 21826 Ventura Blvd., Woodland Hills. (818) 887-6353. Style: 
Neighborhood trattoria -- ideal for weeknight dinners or a Saturday lunch. 
Setting: Pinks with lots of plants. Recommended dishes: Ham calzone; picante 
pizza; rice salad. Cost per person: $10-$20. 
</P>
<P>
Collage, 762 Pacific Ave., Long Beach. (213) 437-3324. Style: One-time gas 
station now pumping a little of this and a little of that. Setting: Bits and 
pieces of artwork. Recommended dishes: Southwestern chicken sandwich; Tunisian 
lamb sausage with cumin and jalapenos; any flavor of the "homemade" ice cream. 
Cost per person: $15-$25. 
</P>
<P>
Orchid, 37 S. Fair Oaks Ave., Pasadena. (818) 796-8787. Style: Hip all-Asian 
for the '80s. Setting: Orchid struts and ducts. Recommended dishes: Chinese 
shrimp toast; Vietnamese lemon grass pork; Thai shrimp curry. Cost per person: 
$10-$20. 
</P>
<P>
Osteria Nonni, 3219 Glendale Blvd., Atwater. (213) 666-7133. Style: Angeli 
clone with a twist of small-town charm. Setting: Pseudo-industrial. Recommended 
dishes: Pizza; croquettes di patate; spaghetti puttanesca. Cost per person: 
$10-$20. 
</P>
<P>
Rive Gauche, 14106 Ventura Blvd., Sherman Oaks. (818) 990-3573. Style: A little 
French restaurant suitable for ladies who lunch. Setting: Quaint, with French 
windows; low beamed ceiling. Recommended dishes: Sweetbreads with shrimp and 
mushrooms in sherry sauce; lamp chops; "death-by-chocolate" cake. Cost per 
person: $12-$25. Kathie Jenkins 
</P>
</TEXT>
