<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUAYLE OPENS MEETING OF NEW SPACE COUNCIL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Vice President Dan Quayle on Friday convened the first meeting of the new 
National Space Council, which is charged with developing a long-range policy 
for America's civil, military and commercial space efforts. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA051489-0089 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 56811 </DOCID>
<DATE>
