<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL HEALTH CLINICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Diego city schools Board of Education is again taking what should be 
valuable planning time to consider whether or not to implement proposed health 
clinics on public school campuses. 
</P>
<P>
Our schools are already teaching sex education and AIDS awareness. They would 
do well to now concentrate on developing and implementing better basic 
educational programs for our children and grandchildren, who to date are being 
taught at a level that is already leading us -- inevitably -- to becoming a 
second-class nation in tomorrow's world. 
</P>
<P>
Our school boards would do well to stay out of moral issues, particularly when 
they are bound so greatly in religious tenets and are considered by a majority 
of us to be a primary parental responsibility. 
</P>
<P>
We want -- we need -- concentration on truly educational courses, better school 
facilities and better teachers receiving substantially better pay, commensurate 
with what should be a professional and honorable career. 
</P>
<P>
