<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ACETONE FLASH FIRE HOSPITALIZES 2 MEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two men were seriously burned Saturday morning in a flash fire at a Sun Valley 
company. Lee Reese, 46, and Enrique Perez, 39, were taken to Pacifica Community 
Hospital and later sent to Sherman Oaks Community Hospital after suffering 
second- and third-degree burns over 70% of their bodies, a Fire Department 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
The men were transferring acetone from one container to another when the 
chemical's vapors flashed. 
</P>
<P>
Firefighters are not sure what caused the flash fire, which caused little 
damage. 
</P>
<P>
The sprinklers at the company, Advanced Packaging Techniques, extinguished the 
fire. 
</P>
</TEXT>
