<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: UCSD TEAM WINS TITLE IN DOUBLES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The UC San Diego doubles team of Christine Behrens and Nancy Calhoun won the 
NCAA Division III national doubles championship Saturday at Claremont-Mudd 
College with a 6-3, 6-4 victory over Julie Kipka and Kathryne Lane of Kenyon 
College of Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
Wednesday, UCSD won the men's team title with an 8-1 victory over Kenyon. 
</P>
<P>
RUNNING 
</P>
<P>
John Rice and Joni Pendleton took first places in the men's and women's open 
divisions of the Palomar Pentathlon at Balboa Stadium. The pentathlon included 
five events -- 200, 400, 800, 1,500 and 3,000 meters -- with an approximate 
rest of 30 minutes between races. Pendleton also won the women's age handicap 
title. Graeme Shirley was the men's handicap winner. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
The second-ranked UC San Diego softball team lost to Calvin College, 3-1, in 
the NCAA Division III regional championship final at Grand Rapids, Mich. 
</P>
<P>
UCSD finished the season with a 35-9 record. Calvin (28-5) advanced to next 
week's NCAA Division III championships at Trenton State, N.J. 
</P>
<P>
US International closed out its season with a nonconference doubleheader loss 
to visiting Cal State Fullerton, 7-2 and 6-2. USIU finished at 15-37. Fullerton 
improved to 45-13. 
</P>
<P>
VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Alicia Turner of USDHS had nine kills and was voted most valuable player after 
leading the West to a 15-11, 8-15, 15-10, 15-12 victory over the East in the 
Mizuno San Diego High School All-Star match at UC San Diego. Blair Noon of San 
Pasqual and Poway's Shannon Griffin had 15 kills apiece for the East. 
</P>
</TEXT>
