<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARGUING THE RACE OF 'THE MOST FASCINATING FIGURE IN HISTORY' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Stanford's claim of Greek/Macedonian/Iranian (Persian) ancestry for Cleopatra 
is historically accurate. Her Ptolemaic ancestry (Greek/Macedonian) goes back 
to Philip II of Macedon, the father of Alexander the Great; she was also 
descended from the Seleucid dynasty of Persia. No historian has discovered any 
trace of African blood in either the Seleucids or Ptolemies. 
</P>
<P>
Just because Cleopatra's father was depicted as black doesn't make him so: Dr. 
Martin Luther King Jr. has been called the second coming of Gandhi, but does 
that make him Indian? 
</P>
<P>
It may interest Kiela Jamal to know that Osiris is a god of vegetation, and as 
such has been depicted with green skin. 
</P>
<P>
JAMES CLINK 
</P>
<P>
Glendora 
</P>
</TEXT>
