Photo, A rose is a rose -- but 65 of them are something else: Children with 
cystic fibrosis often have trouble pronouncing their disease, and it sometimes 
comes out "65 roses." Shirley Rudolph, chairman of the Lawndale Youth Parade, 
took a cue from that and presented an arrangement of 65 roses to Marisol 
Garcia, Cystic Fibrosis Foundation poster child and honorary grand marshal of 
Saturday's parade. ALAN HAGMAN / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
