<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOLLEYBALL COACHES AGREE TO COMPLETE CITY 4-A PLAYOFFS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Coaches of the four volleyball teams left in the City Section 4-A Division 
playoffs agreed Saturday to continue to direct their teams even if teachers 
strike Monday against Los Angeles Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth High Coach Steve Berk made the announcement after a morning meeting, 
saying that he will honor picket lines during the day but join his team for 
practice and matches this week. 
</P>
<P>
Chatsworth will play host to Taft in one semifinal Tuesday at 7 p.m., and 
Westchester will play at Palisades at 4 p.m. in the other. The final is 
scheduled for Friday at UCLA. 
</P>
</TEXT>
