<P>
LOMBARDI'S 8 RBIS PACE TIDEWATER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Phil Lombardi of Granada Hills drove in eight runs Saturday night as the 
Tidewater Tides defeated the Toledo Mud Hens, 10-3, in an International League 
baseball game in Toledo, Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
Lombardi, a graduate of Kennedy High, had a two-run double in the first, a 
three-run double in the second, a two-run double in the third and a run-scoring 
single in the fifth. Tidewater is the triple-A affiliate of the New York Mets. 
</P>
<P>
Lombardi, a first baseman, came within one RBI of tying the single-game league 
record, last achieved in 1963. 
</P>
