<HEADLINE>
<P>
JAPANESE INVESTMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Catherine Collins' article is to the point and she is absolutely right. She 
should be commended for her fortitude in expressing publicly a notion that is 
very unpopular with the real estate industry and, alas, our government. 
</P>
<P>
In an article of mine, published in the January, 1989, issue of the National 
Real Estate Investor magazine, I expressed similar views. 
</P>
<P>
As a concerned citizen, I followed up by writing to some of our elected 
government officials asking them to give this point of view serious thought and 
consideration. So far, it would appear, my appeal fell on deaf ears. 
</P>
<P>
I hope Collins' article might achieve better results. 
</P>
<P>
ALEX LISTON 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
<P>
 Liston is president of Continental Brokerage Co. Inc. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
