<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Philippine soldiers aided by a former Communist rebel found three mass graves 
where the remains of scores of people killed by guerrillas are believed buried, 
a military spokesman said. Those buried in the graves, just south of Manila, 
are thought to have been killed by the Communist New People's Army in a purge 
of suspected spies in their ranks after arrests of rebel leaders last year. 
Reporters said they counted 28 bodies in a mass grave in the town of Kavinti in 
Laguna province. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
