<TEXT>
<P>
A Soviet Politburo commission blamed most of the 25,000 deaths in Armenia's 
earthquake last Dec. 7 on shoddy construction and turned its findings over to 
prosecutors to "file criminal charges and bring those responsible to account," 
the official Tass news agency reported. "The catastrophic consequences of the 
earthquake in Armenia are explained above all by the low quality of the 
building and assembly work, by the inadmissible violation of design norms and 
the strength of underground tremors," Tass said. The report ended an 
investigation that began after the earthquake, which was measured at a 
magnitude of 6.9. The Politburo commission was headed by Premier Nikolai I. 
Ryzhkov. 
</P>
