<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA CRAFT SHOP DESTROYED IN SMOKY DOWNTOWN BLAZE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
VENTURA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A five-alarm fire Saturday destroyed a craft-supply shop in the city's downtown 
shopping district, snarling traffic and spewing a column of black smoke visible 
for miles. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported in the midday blaze at Bonnie's, a store that sold 
spray paints, lacquers and hobby paraphernalia. The fire threatened shops and 
restaurants at the heart of downtown but nearby businesses suffered only smoke 
and water damage, Ventura Fire Chief Bob Horne said. 
</P>
<P>
Horne said the cause of the fire was not known. It spread quickly, he said, 
because of the "volatile nature" of the materials inside. 
</P>
<P>
The shop's roof and mezzanine collapsed, and its entire inventory was burned. 
Fire officials estimated the damage at several hundred thousand dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
FIRES -- VENTURA COUNTY 
</P>
