<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOBILE FREE CLINIC, HEALTH CARE FUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Once again we read (May 3) the news of another part of our health care system 
that is suffering from a lack of funds. This time it is the community 
development council's mobile free clinic. 
</P>
<P>
America, America, where are our values? We hear and read that health care -- 
something that is so necessary to the whole community -- must pay for itself in 
order to survive. I ask this question: why do the Stealth and B-1 bombers not 
have to pay for themselves? Why doesn't the cruise missile pay for itself? 
</P>
<P>
Something is terribly wrong here. 
</P>
<P>
BERNICE RANFORD 
</P>
<P>
Garden Grove 
</P>
