<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRVINE'S RIGHTS LAW AND THE ATTEMPT TO AMEND IT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Herman Wong's article (May 4) is a wonderful example of how good reporting of 
the facts can break through the lies, distortions and myths so frequently 
perpetrated about homosexuals. 
</P>
<P>
Yes, Jim Boone and Joe Bucuzzo are "just like any couple" in Irvine, and, 
indeed, in Orange County. And they are just two of the many thousands of 
committed lesbian and gay couples who live in all parts of our county. 
</P>
<P>
They are also concerned about and assaulted by that small number of virulent 
homophobic people, like (Rep. William E.) Dannemeyer, who would actively deny 
Orange County's lesbians and gay men their full civil and human rights and 
subject them to unfettered discrimination. These people argue that lesbians and 
gay men should be subject to loss of employment or residence due only to the 
whim of a bigoted person. 
</P>
<P>
I am confident that the voters of the city of Irvine will overwhelmingly vote 
for human decency and equal civil rights for all Irvine residents, irrespective 
of their sexual orientation or any other irrelevant factor. 
</P>
<P>
WERNER P. KUHN 
</P>
<P>
Executive Director, Gay and Lesbian Community Services Center of Orange County 
</P>
</TEXT>
